ighted the work of a familiar roster of artists, largely white and male. Over time the achievements of their peers, notably women and artists of color, have gone uncelebrated. The essays in The Unforgettables provide a new and richer understanding of American art as they expand the canon to include many worthy talents, a number of whom were acclaimed in their day, or, having missed that acclaim, may achieve it now. As told by major scholars and museum professionals in the field, The Unforgettables rescues and revises reputations as it enhances and enriches the history of American art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aArt, American. 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh  aamerican art.  aart history.  aart practice.  aartists you should know.  abooks for curators.  acontemporary art.  aessays.  agenerations.  agenius.  ahidden works.  amuseum studies.  anew discoveries.  aunknown.  aunseen.1 aAdams, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAronson, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAter, Renée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBedell, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellion, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoettcher, Graham C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroun, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuick, Kirsten Pai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurdan, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurns, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat